<TITLE> Sample Cover Letter </TITLE>
</HEAD>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/townhall/background.jpg">

<center><h2>Sample Cover Letter </h2></center>
 
1601 Pennsylvania Avenue <br>
Washington,  D.C. 20002 <br>
January 30, 1996<br>
<P>
Ms.  Beth Persons <br>
Intern Coordinator <br>
Heritage Foundation <br>
214 Massachusets Ave. NE <br>
Washington, DC  20002<br>
<P>
Dear Ms. Persons: <br>
 
<p>As an experienced economist who is currently pursuing a master's degree in Economics at Harvard University, I am writing to request information about possible summer internship opportunities with The Heritage Foundation.  I am interested in a position that will allow me to combine the talents I have developed in both political analysis and economics.  However, as you can see from the attached <a href="file:///J|/COMMON/INTERNS/NICKG/resume.htm">resume</a>, I have extensive experience in many related fields, and I always enjoy new challenges. 
 
<p>I feel that it is important for me to maintain a practical, real-world perspective while developing my academic abilities. I am proud of the fact that I have financed my entire education through scholarships and summer jobs related to my field of study.  This work experience has enhanced my appreciation for the education I am pursuing.  I find that I learn as much from my summer jobs as I do from my academic studies.  For example, during the summer of 1995, while working for the National Center for Policy Analysis, I gained a great deal of practical experience in the field of public policy development and critique.  When I returned to school in the fall and took Advanced Policy Analysis, I found that my experience with the NCPA had thoroughly prepared me for the subject. 
 
<p>Having said all this, I realize that your first consideration in hiring an applicant must not be the potential educational experience Heritage can provide, but the skills and services the applicant has to offer.  I hope the experience and education described in my resume suggest how I might be of service to Heritage. 
 
<p>I welcome the opportunity to discuss with you how I might best assist Heritage in fulfilling its present corporate needs.  I will be available for employment from May 14 through August 31, 1996.  Please let me know what summer internship opportunities are available at Heritage for someone with my education, experience, and interests.  You can reach me at the above address or by phone at (518) 555-0000.
<P>
Thank you for your consideration. 
<p>
 
 <ul><ul><ul><ul><ul><ul><blockquote><blockquote>
                                         		Sincerely yours,<br>
<P><br>
                                         		Winthrop Q. Rosenbluth VI <br>
 </ul></ul></ul></ul></ul></ul></blockquote></blockquote>

